headline.main: SEARCHING TAKES AQUEDUCT SPRINT; Talora Gains Other Division of Vagrancy Handicap -- McCreary, Moreno Win SEARCHING FIRST IN AQUEDUCT DASH

results.snippet: Searching and Talora were the winners of the Vagrancy Handicap at Jamaica yesterday. The seven-furlong race for fillies and mares was contested in two divisions, each worth a gross of $28,725, with each of the successful ones earning $19,675.
results.lead_paragraph: Searching and Talora were the winners of the Vagrancy Handicap at Jamaica yesterday. The seven-furlong race for fillies and mares was contested in two divisions, each worth a gross of $28,725, with each of the successful ones earning $19,675.

headline.main: Blue Choir Annexes $104,600 Turf Test; BLUE CHOIR VICTOR IN UNITED NATIONS

results.snippet: ATLANTIC CITY, Sept. 24 -- Blue Choir, the 4-year-old Irish-bred colt owned by Mrs. Harry L. Nathenson of Chicago, won the third running of the rich United Nations Handicap at the Atlantic City Race Track today.
